{"key":"post-9206161","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9206161</id>\n<content>For several years after synthetic filter disks first became available, I put them under the lid.&amp;nbsp; On an intuition, I placed them above the lid to see if that would lower my rate of bacterial contamination, and it did.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Placing the filter under the lid is not a guarantee of failure, nor is placing it above the lid a guarantee of success.&amp;nbsp; However, my rate of failure was higher with the filters, whether tyvek or synthetic filter disk under the lid for the reason that they get damp, and then bacteria can colonize through the filter to reach the grains below.&amp;nbsp; I suggest putting the filter above the lid for your future projects.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>9205182</prev>\n<first>9200523</first>\n<last>9206161</last>\n<when>1226159673</when>\n<utime>11/08/08 05:54 PM</utime>\n</post>"}